WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:34.460 --> 00:00:36.740
﻿Plasma Youth Sports Games
with Unsuccess of the champion,

00:00:36.862 --> 00:00:39.519
would like to thank Slaven Bilić
for stepping in as the host.

00:00:39.606 --> 00:00:43.113
Bilić is one of the first sponsors,
ambassador and is our biggest promoter.

00:00:43.209 --> 00:00:46.049
He used his life and sports experience
in order to prepare high-quality content

00:00:46.170 --> 00:00:48.404
with his guests for all generations.
Thanks, Nane!

00:00:51.060 --> 00:00:54.780
Luka, it's hard to announce you.

00:00:55.060 --> 00:00:59.052
It's hard to say something smart
that you deserve

00:00:59.302 --> 00:01:03.980
and at the same time be careful
not to overdo it.

00:01:05.660 --> 00:01:08.071
However, according to a large
number of opinions, you are

00:01:08.159 --> 00:01:10.555
the best football player
from this region.

00:01:11.660 --> 00:01:17.140
You are the most decorated player
of the biggest club

00:01:17.380 --> 00:01:20.660
in the world, Real Madrid,
and in several categories.

00:01:21.940 --> 00:01:26.620
One of the best midfielders
in football history.

00:01:26.900 --> 00:01:31.700
Despite all that, and it's no less
important, you are certainly

00:01:31.980 --> 00:01:34.700
one of the most beloved players
of your generation.

00:01:34.870 --> 00:01:41.709
Thank you for taking time for us.
-Thank you for the nice intro.

00:01:43.860 --> 00:01:49.940
While I was listening to you,
it all seemed a bit unreal.

00:01:50.140 --> 00:01:54.220
It's like I'm not aware of all that,
but it's nice to hear it.

00:01:54.460 --> 00:01:59.660
That's the truth. I didn't want
to overdo the introduction,

00:01:59.900 --> 00:02:03.700
but I think I've only said
the bare minimum about you.

00:02:03.900 --> 00:02:08.860
It really is...
But we'll talk about that.

00:02:09.100 --> 00:02:16.180
What I noticed is that you're
my sixth guest in a row

00:02:16.500 --> 00:02:21.500
in these Champion's Failure specials.
My guests were all great people.

00:02:22.100 --> 00:02:26.020
Of course, I had to prepare
the least for you because

00:02:26.260 --> 00:02:30.580
we've known each other
our whole lives.

00:02:30.860 --> 00:02:35.580
However, I noticed that you aren't
a frequent guest in the media.

00:02:35.780 --> 00:02:38.540
In that regard, you behave
like Janica Kostelić.

00:02:38.646 --> 00:02:40.846
You're not around much...
More precisely, not at all...

00:02:41.014 --> 00:02:43.294
We have a lot of material
about you daily,

00:02:43.433 --> 00:02:46.793
but it's mostly statements
after matches, quick press

00:02:46.962 --> 00:02:48.962
comments, match previews.

00:02:49.124 --> 00:02:58.284
I noticed you aren't a frequent guest
on shows like this. -You're right.

00:02:59.383 --> 00:03:03.943
I never preferred big interviews.

00:03:04.177 --> 00:03:08.577
Apart from the usual
statements after matches.

00:03:08.754 --> 00:03:12.114
And sometimes before games,
press conferences and such.

00:03:12.314 --> 00:03:16.997
Maybe I had one or two bigger
interviews, but for foreign media.

00:03:17.141 --> 00:03:19.661
I never had one in Croatia.

00:03:19.818 --> 00:03:24.938
Maybe because I have a hard time
gaining trust in people

00:03:25.130 --> 00:03:29.050
and then it's hard for me
to speak openly with everyone.

00:03:29.228 --> 00:03:34.851
Except for one written outlet
in Croatia and one journalist.

00:03:35.241 --> 00:03:38.194
And I've been working with him
for many years

00:03:38.325 --> 00:03:40.859
and I'm always ready
for an interview with him.

00:03:40.978 --> 00:03:42.778
I mean Roberto Matteoni.

00:03:42.885 --> 00:03:44.805
He also wrote the book about me.
-Of course.

00:03:44.905 --> 00:03:50.414
And I haven't done an interview
with him for a year or more.

00:03:50.906 --> 00:03:56.984
It's hard for me to gain trust
and talk openly with people.

00:03:57.186 --> 00:04:01.946
Now that you're a journalist,
it's much easier for me.

00:04:02.115 --> 00:04:03.675
Now you have to.
-It's easier for me.

00:04:03.867 --> 00:04:09.515
I didn't have to, but it's easier.
-You're right. That's why you're special.

00:04:09.664 --> 00:04:14.664
You were like that during
your football career too,

00:04:14.807 --> 00:04:17.726
but we'll talk about that later.

00:04:18.980 --> 00:04:23.983
So, we're currently in Milan,
and you've already settled in.

00:04:24.105 --> 00:04:27.006
I'm not talking about football now,
but about things beyond it.

00:04:27.182 --> 00:04:33.108
Have you started learning Italian?
-Yes. Thank God, I’ve managed well.

00:04:33.255 --> 00:04:37.998
The city is beautiful. People
accepted me phenomenally.

00:04:38.117 --> 00:04:44.037
In the club and outside it.
Teammates and coach. Fans too.

00:04:44.260 --> 00:04:48.020
Everything is at a high level.

00:04:48.823 --> 00:04:53.748
It's immediately clear that
AC Milan is a big club.

00:04:54.776 --> 00:04:58.256
A historic club and one of
the biggest in the world.

00:04:58.426 --> 00:05:02.906
You notice it at every step.
So I'm really happy and enjoying it.

00:05:03.053 --> 00:05:05.693
I understand Italian quite well.

00:05:05.807 --> 00:05:08.022
I still haven't started
learning it with a teacher.

00:05:08.105 --> 00:05:10.022
Are Spanish and Italian
similar languages?

00:05:10.147 --> 00:05:12.569
There are similarities, but
they're not really that close.

00:05:12.769 --> 00:05:15.514
There are similar words,
but not exactly the same.

00:05:15.689 --> 00:05:19.276
It's a big problem for me
when speaking because I still use

00:05:19.403 --> 00:05:23.175
a lot of Spanish words. -But in the end,
everyone understands you.

00:05:23.292 --> 00:05:26.252
Yes, everyone understands
what I want to say.

00:05:26.506 --> 00:05:30.112
I remember when Zvonimir Boban
moved from AC Milan to Celta Vigo,

00:05:30.295 --> 00:05:34.456
and when other players moved
from Italy to Spain, like Jarni,

00:05:34.862 --> 00:05:37.815
the difference was much smaller
than when moving

00:05:37.944 --> 00:05:40.344
from England or Germany to Italy.

00:05:41.436 --> 00:05:46.495
At the very beginning you understand
a lot of words. -That's right.

00:05:46.648 --> 00:05:51.968
I understand a lot when they speak
to me in Italian, especially the coach.

00:05:52.059 --> 00:05:54.956
I understand everything well,
speaking is a bit harder.

00:05:55.102 --> 00:05:57.550
But I think I'll solve that
very quickly too. -Excellent.

00:05:57.803 --> 00:06:02.378
So Milan is now your new
destination after Madrid,

00:06:02.592 --> 00:06:05.952
where you spent 13 years.

00:06:06.109 --> 00:06:13.429
When an athlete plays 13 years,
we say it's a long career.

00:06:13.637 --> 00:06:21.800
Few have such careers.
And you spent 13 years in Madrid.

00:06:22.241 --> 00:06:27.253
I remember your farewell in Madrid,
it was emotional and magnificent.

00:06:28.420 --> 00:06:31.960
You broke all the records,
but that must have

00:06:32.043 --> 00:06:34.243
left some emptiness inside you.

00:06:34.437 --> 00:06:38.881
How did you feel when you
left the club after many years?

00:06:40.140 --> 00:06:42.580
Honestly, it wasn't easy for me.

00:06:42.900 --> 00:06:47.420
I spent a little less than
half my life there.

00:06:48.100 --> 00:06:54.700
In one club, in one city, and it was
one of the best periods of my life.

00:06:55.820 --> 00:07:00.940
We can say that I came to Real
Madrid relatively late, at 27.

00:07:02.700 --> 00:07:05.820
But at the right moment.
-You were ready.

00:07:06.100 --> 00:07:12.500
I was ready for that step. Four years
in England helped me a lot.

00:07:13.940 --> 00:07:18.020
And everything I experienced
and achieved in Madrid

00:07:18.149 --> 00:07:20.269
really seems unreal to me.

00:07:20.456 --> 00:07:23.456
If someone had told me
when I arrived in Madrid:

00:07:23.649 --> 00:07:28.769
"You've come to the biggest club
in the world, in football history.

00:07:29.660 --> 00:07:33.580
Write down what you want
to achieve and what you

00:07:33.820 --> 00:07:37.749
would be satisfied with."
Not only would I not...

00:07:37.920 --> 00:07:41.390
I would have been afraid to write
down everything I achieved.

00:07:41.512 --> 00:07:44.792
So it's really something incredible.

00:07:45.728 --> 00:07:50.248
I don't mean just trophies,
victories or anything else.

00:07:50.504 --> 00:07:54.064
Even the fact that I spent
13 years in such a club.

00:07:54.311 --> 00:07:57.311
I came at 27 and stayed
until almost 40.

00:07:57.503 --> 00:07:59.823
That is something incredible.

00:08:00.329 --> 00:08:03.209
We all know very well
what Real Madrid is.

00:08:03.378 --> 00:08:06.338
It's known that there's no room
for average players.

00:08:06.872 --> 00:08:09.872
To stay in such a club
and at that level

00:08:10.145 --> 00:08:16.530
for so many years is the most
incredible thing for me.

00:08:16.682 --> 00:08:20.282
Along with all the successes
I experienced there.

00:08:20.481 --> 00:08:24.224
That is the greatest success.
-It's incredible to me.

00:08:24.351 --> 00:08:29.381
When I first arrived, I thought
if I stayed five or six years,

00:08:30.006 --> 00:08:35.486
that would be great. Because
careers usually last until 33 or 34.

00:08:35.940 --> 00:08:41.620
Long ago, when I thought about it, I felt
if I played until 35, it would be great.

00:08:41.860 --> 00:08:47.180
And I even exceeded that.
Thank God, I still play well.

00:08:47.380 --> 00:08:50.540
So that's really incredible.

00:08:50.705 --> 00:08:54.000
At one point, it seemed
you might even stay in Madrid.

00:08:56.780 --> 00:09:03.403
It was my wish, I didn't say it
just to flatter the fans,

00:09:03.567 --> 00:09:05.487
the club or anyone else.

00:09:05.672 --> 00:09:09.752
It truly was my big wish
to end my career at Real.

00:09:09.953 --> 00:09:13.913
But everything has
a beginning and an end.

00:09:14.759 --> 00:09:19.122
Sometimes the things you want
don’t come true,

00:09:19.700 --> 00:09:22.940
but regardless of the fact
my wish to retire

00:09:23.140 --> 00:09:27.094
at Real Madrid didn't come true...

00:09:31.200 --> 00:09:36.122
I achieved other things
I never thought I would.

00:09:36.460 --> 00:09:43.083
What had to happen happened.
And I don't regret anything.

00:09:44.081 --> 00:09:47.881
When I saw the farewell
they prepared for me...

00:09:48.420 --> 00:09:52.660
Not even in my most wildest
dreams did I expect that.

00:09:52.900 --> 00:09:57.940
Everything was perfect, very emotional.
Because I'm very emotional too,

00:09:58.260 --> 00:10:02.900
although I don't show it.
I hide it and keep it to myself.

00:10:03.980 --> 00:10:09.220
Those last days in Madrid
were very emotional for me.

00:10:09.566 --> 00:10:14.806
That love from the fans, the club
and all the people connected

00:10:15.023 --> 00:10:20.143
with Real Madrid is something
I’ll remember forever.

00:10:20.540 --> 00:10:22.740
It's truly incredible.

00:10:22.980 --> 00:10:27.580
There are no words to thank
the fans and the club for such

00:10:27.820 --> 00:10:30.780
treatment throughout 13 years.

00:10:30.870 --> 00:10:33.230
They treated me that way
from the first day.

00:10:33.329 --> 00:10:36.453
It didn't start after, say,
"La Decima" or after

00:10:36.568 --> 00:10:38.248
the second Champions League.

00:10:38.378 --> 00:10:42.134
From the beginning when I came
to Real Madrid, no matter how...

00:10:42.263 --> 00:10:45.103
And the difficulties I had.
-And the difficulties you had.

00:10:45.281 --> 00:10:53.403
I felt that love from the fans,
they felt that I was the one.

00:10:54.457 --> 00:11:00.895
And that gave me motivation
and inspiration to give back

00:11:01.125 --> 00:11:04.845
in the best way.
-It was like that everywhere.

00:11:05.110 --> 00:11:10.190
You are one of those people who leave
no option but to love him.

00:11:11.180 --> 00:11:15.340
It left a void for us too.

00:11:15.860 --> 00:11:18.540
For example, everyone who loves
football follows Real Madrid

00:11:18.638 --> 00:11:22.064
and everyone who plays there.
Because Real Madrid is Real Madrid.

00:11:22.198 --> 00:11:26.994
I followed Real Madrid much
more closely for 13 years.

00:11:27.116 --> 00:11:28.962
Which players they signed?

00:11:29.055 --> 00:11:30.815
And which FC Barcelona
or Atlético signed.

00:11:30.947 --> 00:11:33.547
How many points ahead
Real Madrid was.

00:11:33.638 --> 00:11:36.878
You develop a bond with Real Madrid
that goes beyond reason and then,

00:11:37.007 --> 00:11:40.407
suddenly it’s over. Yet you find
yourself following Real Madrid again,

00:11:40.523 --> 00:11:44.939
because it’s Real Madrid. That void
has to exist, it’s inevitable.

00:11:45.187 --> 00:11:48.986
But as an old Chinese proverb says,

00:11:49.175 --> 00:11:53.588
"From the top of the mountain,
every path leads downhill."

00:11:53.989 --> 00:11:56.789
So yes, after Real Madrid,
everything can only go downward.

00:11:57.022 --> 00:12:01.422
However, when the opportunity
with Milan appeared,

00:12:01.511 --> 00:12:07.517
it felt like a natural fit,
almost as if that was it,

00:12:07.657 --> 00:12:13.103
because of the stature of the club and
Milan belonging to that small circle

00:12:13.261 --> 00:12:16.556
of clubs that stand shoulder to shoulder
with, or just beneath, Real Madrid,

00:12:16.672 --> 00:12:20.400
regardless of their current form.
Would you say it’s that kind of a club?

00:12:21.020 --> 00:12:23.620
Absolutely. I completely agree with you.

00:12:23.860 --> 00:12:29.220
I’ve always said that after Real Madrid,
wherever you go, it’s a step down,

00:12:29.460 --> 00:12:32.580
there’s no question about it.
Every player who’s been there

00:12:32.820 --> 00:12:38.380
will tell you the same. But I truly
believe I joined a club whose prestige

00:12:38.517 --> 00:12:40.877
and history place is
very close to Madrid,

00:12:41.039 --> 00:12:45.838
and for me, it was the most ideal
situation imaginable.

00:12:46.031 --> 00:12:50.511
Especially because I’ve loved
Milan since childhood.

00:12:50.728 --> 00:12:53.128
I grew up watching Italian football.

00:12:54.620 --> 00:12:59.889
Milan was always my team,
my favourite club.

00:13:00.500 --> 00:13:04.140
Because of Zvone, or the whole picture?
-It was because of Milan in general,

00:13:04.380 --> 00:13:09.420
but of course, Zvone
was there at the time.

00:13:10.660 --> 00:13:15.140
He had a tremendous career with Milan,
captained the Croatian national team,

00:13:15.380 --> 00:13:23.546
and naturally, his presence made many
Croatians, maybe not all, but most,

00:13:24.041 --> 00:13:30.913
support Milan just as they later
supported Real Madrid when I was there.

00:13:31.663 --> 00:13:39.557
So, when the Milan option
came up, it felt like fate.

00:13:41.189 --> 00:13:44.528
Because it meant
staying at the top level.

00:13:44.731 --> 00:13:48.135
Italian league, in my opinion,
is a highly competitive league,

00:13:48.280 --> 00:13:52.682
one of the toughest in Europe,
where many teams are evenly matched

00:13:52.980 --> 00:13:59.860
and every game is a battle. It was,
frankly, an easy decision for me.

00:14:00.180 --> 00:14:04.475
What also sealed it was the way
the club approached me,

00:14:04.611 --> 00:14:07.335
the people, their openness,
the way they explained the project.

00:14:07.428 --> 00:14:12.265
Everything about it made me feel, yes,
this is it. -And it was a perfect match.

00:14:13.368 --> 00:14:22.483
As much as Milan suited you, they were
equally desperate for a player who could

00:14:22.673 --> 00:14:28.310
bring that spark, someone with
charisma, ambition, and drive,

00:14:28.510 --> 00:14:33.630
which you naturally radiate.
-I agree completely.

00:14:34.740 --> 00:14:40.060
And if I may add, whenever
I used to think hypothetically,

00:14:40.260 --> 00:14:44.078
while I was still at Real Madrid, about
the day I might not be there anymore,

00:14:44.336 --> 00:14:48.579
the first club that always came to mind
was Milan. It was instinctive.

00:14:48.821 --> 00:14:54.603
Whenever I imagined that next chapter,
the answer was always the same: Milan.

00:14:55.380 --> 00:14:58.591
When you were young, actually,
when you were still a child,

00:14:58.794 --> 00:15:06.794
because you’re still young now, Serie A,
at the end of the 1990s, was the league.

00:15:07.267 --> 00:15:10.668
The Premier League hadn’t yet
reached today’s level

00:15:10.895 --> 00:15:14.375
and back then, Serie A was
the creme de la creme, as they say.

00:15:14.537 --> 00:15:18.857
And your idols came from there.
In a way, Serie A raised you.

00:15:19.011 --> 00:15:21.200
One of your idols, if I’m not mistaken,
was Totti, right?

00:15:21.322 --> 00:15:23.480
Yes, Totti was one of my idols.
-Why him?

00:15:23.579 --> 00:15:28.067
I loved the way he played,
the charisma, the personality,

00:15:28.257 --> 00:15:33.387
everything I admire in football.
The creativity, the intelligence,

00:15:33.542 --> 00:15:40.676
the technique. He had it all, and he
embodied everything good about the game.

00:15:40.784 --> 00:15:43.104
That’s why he was one of the players
I adored as a kid,

00:15:43.219 --> 00:15:49.851
along with Zvone later on...
And of course, Zidane and Ronaldo,

00:15:50.039 --> 00:15:53.679
who, to me, was phenomenal, one of my
favourite footballers of all time.

00:15:53.783 --> 00:15:55.663
I wouldn’t say he was an idol per se,

00:15:55.802 --> 00:15:58.562
but as a player,
he’s one of my all-time favourites.

00:15:58.638 --> 00:16:01.878
And back then, everyone played in Italy,
right? -Yes. He also played in Italy.

00:16:02.008 --> 00:16:06.095
He played for Barcelona and Real Madrid,
of course... -But Inter was the thing.

00:16:06.238 --> 00:16:09.079
Exactly. Inter was where
it all happened, until his injury.

00:16:10.060 --> 00:16:15.780
Great. Now, when you compare leagues,
Primera, the Premier League,

00:16:16.780 --> 00:16:22.100
and Serie A today? -They’re all
different, quite different.

00:16:22.460 --> 00:16:28.740
It’s always tricky to compare, but in my
opinion, what I see in Italy is

00:16:29.780 --> 00:16:34.980
a league heavily built around
technical and tactical discipline.

00:16:35.180 --> 00:16:43.300
Especially tactical. Teams are so well-
organized, it’s hard to break them down,

00:16:43.620 --> 00:16:48.180
hard to create chances.
It’s a demanding type of football

00:16:48.500 --> 00:16:53.220
because against any team, you have to
work to earn an opportunity and win.

00:16:53.500 --> 00:16:59.620
That’s what sets it apart
from Spain and England.

00:16:59.820 --> 00:17:02.460
In Spain, the focus is
also on a more technical play,

00:17:02.700 --> 00:17:06.926
in England, it’s that classic
"end-to-end" football,

00:17:07.139 --> 00:17:12.200
fast, physical, running gun football,
non-stop action, intensity everywhere.

00:17:12.297 --> 00:17:15.480
And the spectacle is what they want.
In Spain, if you’re Real Madrid

00:17:15.569 --> 00:17:18.105
and you’re not attacking,
even if you’re leading 2-0,

00:17:18.209 --> 00:17:20.764
the fans start whistling, right?
-True. That expectation is constant.

00:17:20.861 --> 00:17:23.131
Here in Italy, a more pragmatic
approach is tolerated,

00:17:23.270 --> 00:17:26.150
maybe not pure "parking the bus,"
but definitely a more calculated style.

00:17:26.256 --> 00:17:31.084
Exactly. There’s a much stronger
tactical focus. In Spain, of course,

00:17:31.272 --> 00:17:36.318
there’s plenty of transition play
and fast football, as you say,

00:17:36.479 --> 00:17:41.274
especially with Real Madrid during my 13
years there, people were never satisfied

00:17:41.349 --> 00:17:45.786
with just the result. Winning 2-0
wasn’t enough if you weren’t attacking,

00:17:46.011 --> 00:17:49.688
if you were defending yourself.
They demanded a spectacle.

00:17:49.832 --> 00:17:53.157
Right, and that’s what
makes it Real Madrid.

00:17:54.340 --> 00:18:01.580
But anyway, the whole idea
of this show, as you know,

00:18:02.260 --> 00:18:09.500
is to talk not only about your career
but also to show younger generations,

00:18:09.740 --> 00:18:17.787
whether they’re athletes or not,
that success stories like yours

00:18:19.623 --> 00:18:23.867
don’t just happen by chance.
They’re not built on ease or perfection,

00:18:23.979 --> 00:18:28.561
as we say in Dalmatia, "po špagu"
as if everything went smoothly.

00:18:28.694 --> 00:18:32.843
They’re built on challenges,
not necessarily failures,

00:18:32.926 --> 00:18:37.686
but moments where you have to
fight hard, again and again,

00:18:37.778 --> 00:18:40.458
through thorns to reach the stars,
as the saying goes.

00:18:40.558 --> 00:18:46.725
So, to really tell that story properly,
we have to go back to the beginning,

00:18:47.098 --> 00:18:53.818
to your childhood. You were born
in September of 1985, right? -Yes.

00:18:55.500 --> 00:19:01.020
And in your excellent book,
which you co-wrote with Robert Matteoni,

00:19:01.380 --> 00:19:08.420
you describe your childhood
in great detail.

00:19:09.700 --> 00:19:13.660
You remember it vividly,
you talk about your grandfather,

00:19:13.900 --> 00:19:17.780
your upbringing in Zaton Obrovački,
and all those early memories.

00:19:18.040 --> 00:19:22.080
Yes, it wasn’t an easy childhood,

00:19:22.500 --> 00:19:32.180
but when I look back on it,
I can’t say it was an unhappy one.

00:19:32.700 --> 00:19:37.894
Quite the opposite, actually.
I was a happy kid. I enjoyed life.

00:19:38.426 --> 00:19:43.386
Despite the war,
despite the hardships of that time,

00:19:44.140 --> 00:19:51.980
I remember my childhood as a joyful one.
because I was surrounded by friends.

00:19:52.220 --> 00:19:58.717
There were so many of us, because we
were living in a hotel as refugees.

00:20:00.508 --> 00:20:03.966
And all those things
that were happening around us,

00:20:04.119 --> 00:20:08.481
in some way, we were
aware of them, but still...

00:20:08.674 --> 00:20:11.914
You were a child, and life was good.
-Exactly. You had your friends,

00:20:12.030 --> 00:20:15.910
you went outside,
played football all day long,

00:20:15.976 --> 00:20:19.785
did all the things kids do,
hide and seek, games, laughter.

00:20:19.958 --> 00:20:22.518
Of course, you had great time
then... -We had a nice time.

00:20:22.656 --> 00:20:25.456
Do you remember
the time before the war?

00:20:25.606 --> 00:20:28.911
Is that still vivid,
or is it more like a blur now?

00:20:31.703 --> 00:20:35.650
Some things I don’t remember clearly.

00:20:35.879 --> 00:20:40.143
We were living in Zaton near Obrovac,
and when the war started,

00:20:40.309 --> 00:20:44.709
we moved to Zadar, where we lived in
a hotel. I do remember certain moments,

00:20:44.918 --> 00:20:50.158
I remember when my grandfather was
killed, I remember scenes like that.

00:20:50.516 --> 00:20:56.556
Of course, those are things that leave
a mark, and you can’t forget them.

00:20:56.900 --> 00:21:01.980
But again, despite everything,
despite the pain and hardship,

00:21:02.220 --> 00:21:06.860
my childhood was happy. -Of course,
it’s beautiful that you can say that.

00:21:06.950 --> 00:21:09.404
Was football there
from the very beginning?

00:21:09.603 --> 00:21:12.403
Or was it more just sport in general
basketball, maybe, or something else,

00:21:12.557 --> 00:21:16.794
and then later football was the star?
-Football was there from the start.

00:21:17.022 --> 00:21:19.062
I love other sports too,

00:21:19.122 --> 00:21:21.497
I play basketball and I think
I’m pretty decent at it.

00:21:21.625 --> 00:21:25.753
I enjoy tennis and other sports too.
I’ve always been a sports-minded person.

00:21:26.340 --> 00:21:29.060
But football was the one.

00:21:29.300 --> 00:21:33.900
That part in the book
is written beautifully.

00:21:34.220 --> 00:21:43.580
It says that your father, Stipe, once
said how he never got the chance himself

00:21:43.820 --> 00:21:47.580
but that you, his son, will get
the chance, whatever it takes.

00:21:47.820 --> 00:21:51.980
In terms of support, in terms of
sacrifices, even buying you those

00:21:52.126 --> 00:21:55.006
shin guards like Ronaldo’s,
and all the rest...

00:21:55.268 --> 00:22:01.524
Did you, as a kid,
ever feel that pressure?

00:22:01.762 --> 00:22:13.132
That sense that your success might one
day determine your family’s success too?

00:22:16.540 --> 00:22:20.394
Honestly, no.
I didn’t feel pressure back then.

00:22:20.588 --> 00:22:24.597
Mainly because my parents
never put any pressure on me.

00:22:24.842 --> 00:22:32.612
They simply wanted their child, or their
children, to do what they loved,

00:22:33.524 --> 00:22:38.795
to enjoy it, and to be happy. They
wanted to give us everything they could,

00:22:38.976 --> 00:22:42.866
and even more if it meant that I might
have a chance to succeed one day.

00:22:42.960 --> 00:22:47.060
They never imagined it would all turn
into this, what it is today. -Of course.

00:22:47.260 --> 00:22:54.220
But they wanted to be supportive in
everything I was passionate about

00:22:54.500 --> 00:23:00.100
and for me, that was football. Around
that time, when the war was ending

00:23:00.660 --> 00:23:04.900
and people started returning
to their towns and villages,

00:23:05.140 --> 00:23:09.740
rebuilding their homes,
we faced the same decision.

00:23:10.420 --> 00:23:15.180
It was either go back
to our village or stay in Zadar.

00:23:15.420 --> 00:23:18.740
Everyone kept telling my father,

00:23:19.020 --> 00:23:24.140
"Why stay there? Go back home,
there’s nothing for you in the city.

00:23:24.340 --> 00:23:29.940
Forget football." But my parents
made a different decision. We stayed.

00:23:30.140 --> 00:23:35.180
We stayed in the hotel. And, as I said
before, they sacrificed everything,

00:23:36.100 --> 00:23:41.700
absolutely everything, so that
I could keep doing what I loved.

00:23:41.940 --> 00:23:49.100
They deserve the most credit,
especially in those early days.

00:23:49.300 --> 00:23:54.060
All my life, but especially then,
because they could have said "we're done."

00:23:54.300 --> 00:23:58.620
Who knows which path I'd take
and how things would develop after.

00:23:58.820 --> 00:24:04.500
So yes... If I felt pressure,
I didn't feel anything. -Yes.

00:24:04.820 --> 00:24:10.020
I enjoyed what I was doing.
Playing football made me happy.

00:24:10.260 --> 00:24:15.180
I had my dreams. I thought
that one day I would become

00:24:15.420 --> 00:24:21.060
a successful footballer, that I'd
be successful in what I do.

00:24:21.260 --> 00:24:24.180
But if I had pressure or thought
I must do something,

00:24:24.460 --> 00:24:31.260
no, I didn't have that. But I wanted
to somehow give back

00:24:31.540 --> 00:24:38.100
to my parents, and I was fully
focused. I wanted to do everything

00:24:38.740 --> 00:24:47.340
to reach what I wanted. -That's
important. It shaped your character.

00:24:47.580 --> 00:24:52.580
My grandma used to say: what you
learn by third grade is what you know.

00:24:55.760 --> 00:25:00.500
That's it. Your situation...
then not in Zadar, but later

00:25:00.700 --> 00:25:06.060
in Dinamo, as a junior or cadet...
You're the oldest child, right?

00:25:06.860 --> 00:25:12.460
You have two sisters, the only son.
And Janica said she never felt

00:25:12.740 --> 00:25:17.260
as a child that they lacked money
or lived without wealth.

00:25:17.500 --> 00:25:23.594
Whether you like it or not, that
builds character and responsibility.

00:25:24.204 --> 00:25:29.660
I won't say an obligation. Parents
do it out of love, of course,

00:25:30.060 --> 00:25:33.660
but because of that love, you want
to give back and do something

00:25:33.860 --> 00:25:39.180
for all of you, in the end.
-Yes, that's true.

00:25:39.420 --> 00:25:47.140
I wanted to give the maximum I could,
to repay my parents for the support

00:25:47.340 --> 00:25:54.260
and their sacrifice.
That was my guiding thought.

00:25:54.460 --> 00:26:00.460
There was no pressure
that I must succeed.

00:26:00.860 --> 00:26:06.460
You know those guys.
I've seen it a hundred times.

00:26:07.420 --> 00:26:12.740
Dudu and Ćorluka are very similar.
When you three arrived

00:26:12.980 --> 00:26:17.820
to our U-21 team,
it was almost a copy-paste.

00:26:18.020 --> 00:26:21.780
Except of course for Dudu,
there's no war in Brazil,

00:26:22.020 --> 00:26:25.220
but he has a big family.
He's the only one who at 15,

00:26:25.351 --> 00:26:27.632
you know this better,
came to Zagreb.

00:26:27.761 --> 00:26:34.007
Ćarli’s family from Derventa
overnight, a huge family, five boys.

00:26:35.660 --> 00:26:39.460
Whether you like it or not, you
carry that responsibility inside,

00:26:39.660 --> 00:26:46.300
that the future is on you. Not just
yours, but your whole family’s.

00:26:46.517 --> 00:26:52.757
It's easy to break there.
But if you succeed, it's the world.

00:26:53.060 --> 00:26:59.524
Then you're Rocky. -I agree.
I wanted them to be proud of me.

00:27:00.071 --> 00:27:04.020
To be proud of their child,
that they raised him right,

00:27:04.260 --> 00:27:10.740
that he did what they maybe
expected from him,

00:27:10.839 --> 00:27:13.039
because they believed in him.

00:27:13.769 --> 00:27:17.569
That mattered to me. For my parents
to be proud and happy.

00:27:17.762 --> 00:27:20.962
I also have my children, and I know
that when they do something good,

00:27:21.092 --> 00:27:23.425
there’s no greater joy. -Yes.

00:27:23.575 --> 00:27:26.735
No greater wealth.
That was my motivation.

00:27:26.912 --> 00:27:31.503
As we say here, conditions
weren’t ideal or easy.

00:27:31.632 --> 00:27:36.831
Not the best conditions. For example,
you in Zadar, as you said,

00:27:37.524 --> 00:27:43.524
you had a ball. -We had.
-You had a kit. One pair of shin guards.

00:27:43.669 --> 00:27:49.535
Those as Ronaldo. You had them.
To the pitch you had to walk or bike.

00:27:49.667 --> 00:27:53.987
You have all that, but not too much.
For anything else you can’t lie back,

00:27:54.282 --> 00:28:00.202
you have to earn it. -Yes.
-You have to bite, right?

00:28:00.428 --> 00:28:06.348
That’s common. Croatian athletes
respond best when conditions are tough.

00:28:06.736 --> 00:28:11.496
I’ve seen it a million times.
Even before matches.

00:28:11.728 --> 00:28:16.865
When everything is good,
top hotel, top everything…

00:28:17.309 --> 00:28:22.810
Suddenly it drops. When something
keeps you on edge... -Stress, nerves.

00:28:22.972 --> 00:28:25.529
You function better
than when everything is relaxed.

00:28:25.657 --> 00:28:27.578
It’s remarkable. -It is.

00:28:29.940 --> 00:28:38.980
So, you're in Zadar. Then comes
a moment I'd like to clarify. Hajduk.

00:28:41.060 --> 00:28:47.572
That's Zadar’s region. People there
supported Zadar, of course.

00:28:47.726 --> 00:28:52.646
But it's Hajduk. Most people
support Hajduk.

00:28:54.340 --> 00:28:58.980
You were invited to a Hajduk
tournament or something. -Yes.

00:28:59.205 --> 00:29:03.565
Then you get… Hajduk don’t take you,
you must return to Zadar.

00:29:03.719 --> 00:29:08.119
Then the coach in Zadar puts you
"on ice", as punishment.

00:29:08.258 --> 00:29:11.364
How was that?
Do you remember?

00:29:12.100 --> 00:29:17.140
Well, first of all, in Dalmatia
almost everyone supports Hajduk.

00:29:17.420 --> 00:29:22.780
I did too, especially my dad.
The chance opened to go

00:29:23.100 --> 00:29:30.660
to Hajduk for training camp.
To go to Hajduk, stay with them,

00:29:31.100 --> 00:29:36.140
start playing for Hajduk.
That chance opened,

00:29:36.390 --> 00:29:43.830
and my dad did it without telling
the late Tomislav Bašić.

00:29:43.991 --> 00:29:51.591
I went with my current best man,
Oštrić, we were there together.

00:29:51.980 --> 00:29:57.580
We stayed maybe two weeks.
We had some matches,

00:29:57.733 --> 00:29:59.733
trainings and all that.

00:29:59.887 --> 00:30:04.927
People at Hajduk decided then
that it was too early for me.

00:30:05.206 --> 00:30:11.486
For whatever reason… -Grgurević
was already there? -He was.

00:30:12.380 --> 00:30:17.380
When I was there, I felt I was
on that level, that...

00:30:17.620 --> 00:30:22.180
That you belonged there. -That I
could see I was the one. We played

00:30:22.420 --> 00:30:30.180
many matches, Zadar vs Hajduk,
Šibenik. We mostly won.

00:30:30.420 --> 00:30:34.500
We beat Hajduk, Šibenik,
and other Croatian clubs.

00:30:34.700 --> 00:30:37.860
We had a good generation.
I felt it was right.

00:30:38.060 --> 00:30:42.420
But Hajduk decided
it was still too early.

00:30:42.660 --> 00:30:47.220
Maybe due to pressure
from Zadar, because then

00:30:47.420 --> 00:30:51.500
the late Tomislav Bašić had
big influence in football.

00:30:51.740 --> 00:30:56.000
He was avant-garde,
ahead of his time.

00:30:56.106 --> 00:30:58.843
He got angry about it.
At my dad, mainly,

00:30:58.951 --> 00:31:01.471
because he took me
without telling him.

00:31:02.980 --> 00:31:07.140
OK, what happened happened.
I didn’t pass, I returned to Zadar.

00:31:07.332 --> 00:31:10.932
Of course there was disappointment.

00:31:11.111 --> 00:31:16.511
You must return to Zadar. That
disappointment of "you’re not that good".

00:31:17.180 --> 00:31:22.060
Not good enough,
now you return to us.

00:31:24.060 --> 00:31:28.020
I expected that when I returned
I'd continue training.

00:31:28.220 --> 00:31:31.140
We move on, as if nothing happened.
It didn’t discourage me,

00:31:31.380 --> 00:31:37.980
but it did touch the ego…
-It cut you down. -Yes.

00:31:38.860 --> 00:31:44.180
But the late Tomo Bašić told
my dad no. If he's not good enough

00:31:44.420 --> 00:31:48.740
for Hajduk, he's not good enough
for us. And he can’t train.

00:31:49.020 --> 00:31:55.020
Then my dad asked why, how.
No, he can't train for three months.

00:31:55.460 --> 00:32:02.094
Let him work... Back then he had
special exercises. Let him hang

00:32:02.914 --> 00:32:09.155
on the fence to stretch out,
so he could grow. Did it help?

00:32:09.409 --> 00:32:15.108
I don’t know. Those three months
I couldn’t train. Imagine that.

00:32:15.269 --> 00:32:20.429
I love football, it’s everything,
and you can’t go train with friends.

00:32:21.083 --> 00:32:24.723
But I used that time to do
what he told me to do.

00:32:24.939 --> 00:32:29.539
I played every day on the parking
lot in front of the hotel, at school.

00:32:29.857 --> 00:32:35.257
That’s how I compensated for
not being allowed to train.

00:32:35.443 --> 00:32:40.883
My dad went completely crazy.
They had a great relationship,

00:32:41.380 --> 00:32:46.260
but he got a bit upset. You’re
forbidding his child to train. -Yes.

00:32:46.660 --> 00:32:52.980
Maybe he thought he was ruining me
or stopping my career.

00:32:53.980 --> 00:32:57.616
But after 2-3 months they talked
and sorted everything out.

00:32:57.802 --> 00:33:04.460
I went back to training in Zadar.
After that I went to Dinamo.

00:33:04.704 --> 00:33:10.991
That’s the reason I didn’t stay
in Hajduk. The exact reason,

00:33:11.245 --> 00:33:14.335
as I said before, I don't know.
They simply decided

00:33:14.485 --> 00:33:16.885
it was too early for me,
that I wasn’t ready yet.

00:33:17.055 --> 00:33:21.835
Then that story appeared again,
the same one as today,

00:33:22.088 --> 00:33:25.624
more or less. I don’t know
what it was then,

00:33:25.737 --> 00:33:29.710
but it followed you.
Later you carried that stigma

00:33:29.800 --> 00:33:33.200
for quite some time, as if you
weren’t physically strong enough,

00:33:33.307 --> 00:33:38.210
that you weren’t it. Did that,
not now, but back then,

00:33:38.311 --> 00:33:44.952
do you remember, you said it
didn’t shake you. Did it maybe...

00:33:45.051 --> 00:33:48.251
That can shake you on that path
when someone tells you that.

00:33:48.399 --> 00:33:54.358
Or were you uncompromising,
believing it was irrelevant.

00:33:54.643 --> 00:34:00.654
No, it didn’t shake me at all,
didn’t plant any doubt in me

00:34:01.387 --> 00:34:09.360
that maybe it was true. I really
always had great faith in myself.

00:34:09.772 --> 00:34:13.211
It followed me not only in those
younger years, but also when

00:34:13.462 --> 00:34:17.222
I came to Dinamo, when I left
for England. -Yes. -And later

00:34:17.337 --> 00:34:20.719
even in Real. Through my whole
career. It followed me

00:34:20.807 --> 00:34:25.919
until I won the Ballon d’Or.
Then they said, maybe that’s it.

00:34:26.039 --> 00:34:29.919
I’m exaggerating a bit,
but that’s how it was.

00:34:31.557 --> 00:34:37.677
It was only motivation for me
to continue. As a person

00:34:38.098 --> 00:34:44.338
through those younger periods
and later, as I grew and got older,

00:34:44.900 --> 00:34:51.740
I didn’t care about others’ opinions.
-Nothing? -OK, you listen,

00:34:51.886 --> 00:34:57.926
you hear, but it motivated me.
Especially negative opinions.

00:34:58.096 --> 00:35:02.347
I always held on to the positive
ones, because there were such.

00:35:02.442 --> 00:35:04.642
You can’t say everything
was negative.

00:35:05.073 --> 00:35:12.792
But it never... If I had cared
about others’ opinions,

00:35:14.045 --> 00:35:18.355
especially such judgments,
because my opinion of myself

00:35:18.823 --> 00:35:22.480
wasn’t like that. Another thing
would be if I also thought

00:35:22.730 --> 00:35:26.846
that I was short or weak.
My opinion was the opposite.

00:35:26.998 --> 00:35:31.707
Football isn’t just strength
and height. Football is much

00:35:32.006 --> 00:35:37.726
more than strength alone, that
you must be 1.90 meters tall,

00:35:37.849 --> 00:35:41.169
that you must run 100 meters
in 11 or 12 seconds.

00:35:41.300 --> 00:35:47.420
No, football is much more.
Technique, mind… -Feeling. -Feeling.

00:35:47.705 --> 00:35:53.324
Much more of everything else.
And today when I watch football,

00:35:53.416 --> 00:36:03.069
again people try to push that
aggression, speed, strength.

00:36:03.288 --> 00:36:06.522
Today everything is measured.
-Everything is measured, but it’s not.

00:36:06.674 --> 00:36:09.483
But no, in football,
the mind is the most important.

00:36:09.613 --> 00:36:15.163
And it always will be. Strength
and speed will never replace

00:36:15.375 --> 00:36:20.695
technique and intelligence,
because that’s what people

00:36:21.060 --> 00:36:25.315
truly love about football.
Because of those things.

00:36:25.437 --> 00:36:27.477
Well said, Luka.

00:36:30.100 --> 00:36:35.420
You mentioned Tomislav Bašić
several times as your football father,

00:36:35.700 --> 00:36:40.287
and you mentioned him again now,
but unfortunately he passed away.

00:36:40.439 --> 00:36:42.679
You also went to his funeral.

00:36:43.999 --> 00:36:53.353
At that age, the role of a coach
is much greater. You listen

00:36:53.620 --> 00:36:58.020
to him more than your parents
in those adolescent years?

00:36:58.376 --> 00:37:02.783
Was he a special person?
-He was special, truly special.

00:37:02.956 --> 00:37:05.796
As I said earlier,
he was ahead of his time.

00:37:06.199 --> 00:37:13.400
He understood football
on a very high level.

00:37:13.778 --> 00:37:16.720
And for me, he was special
because he was one

00:37:16.888 --> 00:37:21.924
of the rare people who believed
in me from the very beginning.

00:37:22.240 --> 00:37:27.840
When others were saying the things
you mentioned earlier... -Yes.

00:37:28.260 --> 00:37:32.700
He was by my side from the start.
He believed in me,

00:37:32.980 --> 00:37:38.002
and he always told me where
I would go and what I would achieve.

00:37:38.218 --> 00:37:42.573
He was always there for me,
even when others didn’t believe in me

00:37:42.732 --> 00:37:45.732
and were skeptical. He never was.
Right from the start.

00:37:45.855 --> 00:37:49.221
He was one of the few people,
besides my family,

00:37:49.407 --> 00:37:52.987
and among coaches he was truly
one of the rare ones.

00:37:53.217 --> 00:37:56.337
I don’t want to be unfair and
say there were no others,

00:37:56.552 --> 00:37:59.526
but with him I had a special bond.

00:37:59.788 --> 00:38:04.108
My football father and I were
close even outside football.

00:38:04.339 --> 00:38:07.699
His son was also my coach
in the younger categories,

00:38:07.923 --> 00:38:13.041
so that connection was really
something incredible,

00:38:13.900 --> 00:38:24.630
and the gratitude I feel for him
can’t be expressed in words.

00:38:24.840 --> 00:38:27.880
So yes, it was truly
something unbelievable.

00:38:31.060 --> 00:38:34.700
So he was the link to Dinamo,
and that’s how you went there.

00:38:35.140 --> 00:38:39.900
And the separation from your mom
and sisters was emotional,

00:38:40.180 --> 00:38:44.380
wasn’t it, when you had to
leave for Zagreb? -Yes.

00:38:44.789 --> 00:38:48.669
He recommended me to Dinamo
and to Zdravko, who at that

00:38:48.783 --> 00:38:51.001
time was the number one
person in the club.

00:38:51.161 --> 00:38:53.995
He recommended me,
and Zdravko didn’t even know me.

00:38:54.116 --> 00:38:57.136
None of them knew much about me.
They took him at his word.

00:38:57.267 --> 00:39:01.722
Yes, Zdravko trusted him.
-Yes, he did. That’s how it was.

00:39:01.900 --> 00:39:07.780
And leaving my family
was difficult, honestly.

00:39:08.020 --> 00:39:15.060
My sisters, my mom, my dad…
Leaving Zadar for Zagreb.

00:39:15.417 --> 00:39:23.372
Back then, without highways,
it was almost a five-hour drive.

00:39:24.220 --> 00:39:29.228
A long trip. And even though
the ride passed quickly,

00:39:31.392 --> 00:39:36.818
the goodbye was not easy.
Everyone cried - my sisters,

00:39:37.060 --> 00:39:41.420
my dad, who is very emotional
and can’t hold it in.

00:39:41.620 --> 00:39:45.820
He let everything out.

00:39:46.300 --> 00:39:51.860
My mom was the most composed,
even though she’s emotional too,

00:39:52.100 --> 00:39:54.980
but she’s more like me,
she keeps it inside.

00:39:55.220 --> 00:40:00.220
But when I got into the car, because
I didn’t want to cry in front of them,

00:40:00.420 --> 00:40:02.940
the tears started coming
for me too.

00:40:03.180 --> 00:40:05.740
Because you're leaving behind
your friends, childhood,

00:40:05.980 --> 00:40:10.540
and you're going to a new city
where you have to meet new friends,

00:40:11.460 --> 00:40:15.100
but I knew where I was going
and I wanted to progress.

00:40:15.380 --> 00:40:18.540
You were ready for that step.
-I was ready.

00:40:18.780 --> 00:40:22.933
It wasn't easy, but when you
know what you want,

00:40:23.785 --> 00:40:30.220
everything becomes much easier.
-You arrive in Zagreb, a big city,

00:40:30.500 --> 00:40:35.460
Dinamo a top club at that time.
At the academy run by Zdravko,

00:40:35.740 --> 00:40:43.020
everything was perfectly organized.
You develop normally, right?

00:40:43.220 --> 00:40:45.380
You adapt to everything,

00:40:45.620 --> 00:40:50.860
and then comes that period
which is, how should I put it,

00:40:51.100 --> 00:40:55.860
not really exciting and it kind of
goes under the radar, I'd say.

00:40:56.060 --> 00:40:59.220
But that's actually the most
important period, when your

00:40:59.389 --> 00:41:02.949
youth career ends, and so many
players get lost there,

00:41:03.095 --> 00:41:05.775
because it's the hardest
transition... -Yes.

00:41:06.038 --> 00:41:10.435
... the transition from youth
to senior football, and for you,

00:41:10.997 --> 00:41:14.340
everything was basically going fine.

00:41:14.900 --> 00:41:18.660
The move to Zrinjski,
from today's perspective,

00:41:18.860 --> 00:41:21.860
sounds like one of the best
decisions. -Yes.

00:41:22.060 --> 00:41:25.878
But at the time, it was a huge risk.
It was a ticking time bomb,

00:41:26.002 --> 00:41:28.034
because you were going
to another country,

00:41:28.148 --> 00:41:30.542
to a league that is tough
and unforgiving, right?

00:41:31.260 --> 00:41:36.374
How did you feel back then?
-It just happened that way.

00:41:36.722 --> 00:41:43.257
As you said yourself, that move
from juniors to seniors

00:41:43.900 --> 00:41:51.580
is complicated, and a lot of players
get lost there. In my opinion,

00:41:52.300 --> 00:41:58.900
that happens because in
that period they don't play,

00:41:59.180 --> 00:42:02.940
they stay where it's easier,
where they're in their comfort zone,

00:42:03.180 --> 00:42:06.030
and then they're not ready
to take that step,

00:42:06.193 --> 00:42:10.353
to maybe even go one level down,
so they can eventually rise back up.

00:42:11.438 --> 00:42:14.373
And in my opinion, that might be
part of the problem.

00:42:15.062 --> 00:42:18.262
But when that opportunity appeared,
I immediately wanted

00:42:18.402 --> 00:42:22.402
to go to Zrinjski. I knew I was going
to a professional league,

00:42:22.642 --> 00:42:26.882
and I thought that was better for me,
because I would be competing

00:42:27.060 --> 00:42:31.340
in senior football, and I wouldn't
remain among the juniors.

00:42:31.586 --> 00:42:37.826
At that time, Dinamo were forming
their second team, but they

00:42:38.300 --> 00:42:42.134
would have played against second-
division and third-division sides...

00:42:42.711 --> 00:42:45.579
You'd be with your friends,
it would be nice, comfortable,

00:42:45.768 --> 00:42:48.069
in your comfort zone...
But would you really improve?

00:42:48.253 --> 00:42:51.826
That's the real question.
-And was going to Zrinjski your decision?

00:42:52.524 --> 00:42:57.716
No, a few players had already
gone to Zrinjski,

00:42:57.992 --> 00:43:02.177
and then they asked if I would
come too. I said I would,

00:43:02.342 --> 00:43:05.931
because Landeka and Đidić had gone,
and I had a very good relationship

00:43:06.014 --> 00:43:07.717
with both of them.

00:43:08.368 --> 00:43:11.781
The club director at that time
was Đidić’s father, so they also

00:43:12.011 --> 00:43:15.523
asked me if I would come.
I agreed, and I went down there,

00:43:15.723 --> 00:43:20.790
and the rest, as they say, is history.
And things were fantastic for me there.

00:43:20.982 --> 00:43:25.382
It was one of the best decisions
I made, even though from

00:43:25.923 --> 00:43:29.883
today’s perspective it might
seem a bit risky.

00:43:29.995 --> 00:43:31.835
But I didn’t see it that way.

00:43:31.973 --> 00:43:36.645
I saw it as an opportunity
to prove myself. -I understand.

00:43:36.820 --> 00:43:40.180
That’s how I approached it,
and it turned out to be phenomenal.

00:43:40.380 --> 00:43:44.940
It helped you that, very soon,
Štef Deverić came in as coach,

00:43:45.140 --> 00:43:47.660
and he had been your coach
in the youth team. -Yes.

00:43:47.900 --> 00:43:52.660
He came very quickly, maybe after
five or six rounds. -Yes.

00:43:52.900 --> 00:43:59.180
Although even with the previous coach,
Franjo Đidić, we worked very well.

00:43:59.420 --> 00:44:01.780
I felt good there from the first day.

00:44:02.020 --> 00:44:05.580
I remember the situation
when I came to Zrinjski

00:44:06.420 --> 00:44:11.100
and the first match was approaching.
You know how it used to be, after training,

00:44:11.340 --> 00:44:14.894
and before the match the next day,
they'd give you the list of players

00:44:15.046 --> 00:44:17.876
who would play, those included
in the squad. The first eighteen.

00:44:18.003 --> 00:44:20.550
Now, whether you would play
or not wasn’t the point,

00:44:20.672 --> 00:44:22.827
but I had gone there to play.

00:44:24.320 --> 00:44:28.186
So everyone is reading the names,
and I’m not on the list.

00:44:29.961 --> 00:44:33.850
And no one says anything to me.
When training finished,

00:44:34.340 --> 00:44:38.460
I went to the showers
and the tears started.

00:44:38.784 --> 00:44:42.467
I was disappointed, because
I thought I had come there to play,

00:44:42.666 --> 00:44:44.866
and the coach didn’t
even put me on the list.

00:44:45.068 --> 00:44:48.268
Under the shower, alone,
I’m crying and praying to God

00:44:48.445 --> 00:44:51.178
that no one walks in and sees me.

00:44:51.426 --> 00:44:54.952
Then somehow I calmed down,
got dressed, got ready,

00:44:55.047 --> 00:44:57.367
and went home
completely disappointed.

00:44:57.506 --> 00:45:01.546
Then they called me and said:
"You're not on the list

00:45:01.724 --> 00:45:04.324
because your documents
didn’t arrive in time."

00:45:05.055 --> 00:45:08.415
That was a huge relief.
Okay, so it’s not bad after all.

00:45:08.671 --> 00:45:13.631
That’s one of the anecdotes. After that,
everything started going great.

00:45:13.800 --> 00:45:17.512
Stjepan Deverić arrived,
and we had a really good season.

00:45:17.651 --> 00:45:19.931
At first, we were fighting
to stay up, but in the end

00:45:20.100 --> 00:45:22.940
we finished somewhere
mid-table, maybe 7th or 8th.

00:45:23.172 --> 00:45:27.544
But that period in Mostar
shaped me as a person,

00:45:27.726 --> 00:45:30.766
it toughened me a lot, because
the league was, as I’ve said

00:45:30.943 --> 00:45:35.743
a hundred times, ruthless,
with very aggressive opponents.

00:45:35.935 --> 00:45:39.175
That helped me as
a young player... -Yes, yes.

00:45:39.493 --> 00:45:46.093
... to grow and to see that I
could handle senior football.

00:45:46.500 --> 00:45:49.420
Those were intense years.

00:45:49.557 --> 00:45:54.025
We talked about that - that’s the
period when many players get lost,

00:45:54.219 --> 00:45:57.339
but you, after a year in Zrinjski,
went to Inter Zaprešić.

00:45:57.549 --> 00:46:00.502
And again, luck was waiting
for you there,

00:46:00.628 --> 00:46:02.822
luck that you had no control over.

00:46:02.982 --> 00:46:05.397
Because you didn’t know that
Štef Deverić would come in

00:46:05.520 --> 00:46:07.728
as the coach, and yet things
turned out that way.

00:46:07.840 --> 00:46:10.807
You arrive at Inter, where
Čeči Bogdan is also a very

00:46:11.020 --> 00:46:14.300
pleasant man, a gentleman,
articulate, loves to talk...

00:46:14.540 --> 00:46:18.260
Phenomenal. -Supportive
of young players…

00:46:18.460 --> 00:46:22.980
And suddenly, you’re fighting
for the title... -Yes. -Right?

00:46:23.117 --> 00:46:25.037
After only six months there.

00:46:25.198 --> 00:46:29.597
At the same time, Aljoša and I
arrive in the U-21 national team,

00:46:29.764 --> 00:46:33.401
people who don’t follow
the old rule that in the youth

00:46:33.530 --> 00:46:36.073
national team only players
who are exactly 21 must play,

00:46:36.221 --> 00:46:38.574
but that someone who is 18
can also play.

00:46:38.666 --> 00:46:41.506
We recognized a few of you
and called you up.

00:46:42.900 --> 00:46:48.083
After that, your return
to Dinamo followed,

00:46:48.420 --> 00:46:51.153
after six months, at a moment
when Dinamo were

00:46:51.266 --> 00:46:53.723
"worse than ever -
the league of fools."

00:46:53.849 --> 00:46:57.505
Yes. -You returned, but not
"quietly through the back door",

00:46:57.919 --> 00:47:01.794
you were given the keys
to make a difference.

00:47:02.313 --> 00:47:06.637
That’s three dressing rooms
in two years, that’s difficult.

00:47:06.806 --> 00:47:09.255
All of that happened
in a year and a half.

00:47:09.816 --> 00:47:16.856
Yes, but I have to say that,
as we mentioned earlier,

00:47:17.540 --> 00:47:22.220
I was one of the few from
the ’85 and ’84 generations

00:47:22.420 --> 00:47:24.620
who didn’t get an early
chance at Dinamo.

00:47:24.860 --> 00:47:27.940
I didn’t go even once to preseason
with Dinamo’s first team,

00:47:28.180 --> 00:47:30.900
while there were players who did,
and we were the same age.

00:47:31.039 --> 00:47:33.559
How could you go, when you
left for Zrinjski at 18?

00:47:33.682 --> 00:47:38.122
Well, yes, but if you believe I’m the one,
maybe you can take me along,

00:47:38.439 --> 00:47:42.039
and then see whether I could impose
myself and whether I have the quality.

00:47:42.247 --> 00:47:44.687
But that trust wasn’t there.

00:47:46.420 --> 00:47:49.060
I went to Zrinjski.

00:47:49.340 --> 00:47:53.060
I played a phenomenal season
there and came back,

00:47:53.300 --> 00:47:56.460
but again I didn't go to training,
for example, with Dinamo,

00:47:56.740 --> 00:48:00.540
but I went on loan to Inter.
That wasn't bad for me.

00:48:00.654 --> 00:48:02.958
On the contrary, that helped me.
I wanted that.

00:48:03.045 --> 00:48:06.005
I didn't refuse it and say
I didn't want to go to training.

00:48:06.182 --> 00:48:10.677
You didn't feel like
a generational talent? -I did.

00:48:10.833 --> 00:48:15.833
Yes, but you weren't recognized
by them? -I wasn't treated that way.

00:48:16.144 --> 00:48:22.905
The players who got the chance
all went to training.

00:48:23.343 --> 00:48:26.913
Maybe not all of them,
not to mention names.

00:48:27.112 --> 00:48:32.260
But I don't have
a bad opinion about it.

00:48:32.452 --> 00:48:37.492
Because you knew you were better
than those who went to training?

00:48:37.780 --> 00:48:40.333
That was my thinking.

00:48:40.784 --> 00:48:44.892
The late Tomo Bašić
didn’t want me to leave.

00:48:45.044 --> 00:48:47.705
He said I should go
straight to Dinamo.

00:48:47.953 --> 00:48:53.244
He kept saying I was "the one",
but that's irrelevant.

00:48:53.689 --> 00:48:59.322
The experience in Zrinjski
built me up as a player,

00:49:00.302 --> 00:49:06.822
it helped me a lot. Going to Inter
created a phenomenal team.

00:49:07.140 --> 00:49:13.580
Čarli went with me,
Čale and Janjetović.

00:49:14.001 --> 00:49:19.466
There were a few of us from Dinamo.
An incredible squad was created.

00:49:19.700 --> 00:49:25.620
In the first six rounds we had six wins.
We even beat Dinamo in Zaprešić.

00:49:27.660 --> 00:49:31.620
And everything went well until
mid-season, we were even first.

00:49:31.860 --> 00:49:37.143
Yes, we were first and Dinamo
decided to bring me back

00:49:37.567 --> 00:49:44.127
in that winter transfer window.
I wanted to stay at Inter at that time.

00:49:44.384 --> 00:49:47.784
I wanted to stay, because
we were playing well.

00:49:47.961 --> 00:49:50.321
We were fighting
for the championship.

00:49:50.467 --> 00:49:55.893
I returned to Dinamo for half a season.
I never liked returning halfway through.

00:49:56.447 --> 00:50:00.247
You either start from
the beginning or you don't.

00:50:00.354 --> 00:50:03.434
But Dinamo decided
to bring me back.

00:50:03.603 --> 00:50:07.523
It was probably influenced
by Niko’s move to Hajduk.

00:50:08.660 --> 00:50:13.500
And then my worst half-season
at Dinamo happened,

00:50:13.662 --> 00:50:16.302
where we were playing
in a meaningless league.

00:50:16.441 --> 00:50:19.241
I played one or two games
and then got injured.

00:50:19.464 --> 00:50:22.485
That is the only period when
I was glad to be injured.

00:50:22.765 --> 00:50:28.539
Because there was chaos in the club.
When you look at it from perspective,

00:50:28.689 --> 00:50:31.449
when all that is over,
then everything is great.

00:50:31.626 --> 00:50:36.106
However, as you said, the third locker
room in a year and a half is Dinamo,

00:50:36.291 --> 00:50:43.987
where Niko Kranjčar goes from Dinamo.
He was actually kicked out of Dinamo. -Yes.

00:50:47.020 --> 00:50:52.300
A top player, a legend,
the greatest talent leaves.

00:50:52.510 --> 00:50:55.110
And then you come along...

00:50:56.560 --> 00:51:01.258
People had nothing against you,
of course, but they had against Niko.

00:51:03.620 --> 00:51:07.900
That's a lot of pressure for you.

00:51:08.460 --> 00:51:16.624
Yes, it was a burden, even though
there was chaos in the club.

00:51:18.180 --> 00:51:21.940
And in the team, among the players,
there was a bad atmosphere.

00:51:22.140 --> 00:51:26.635
I don't want to remember
that six-month period.

00:51:26.966 --> 00:51:33.925
Did you deliberately put him aside?
-Yes. But it was the way it was.

00:51:35.466 --> 00:51:42.915
Every experience strengthens you
somehow. You toughen up...

00:51:43.225 --> 00:51:44.632
When it passes.

00:51:45.177 --> 00:51:49.119
So in that six-month period,
I learned something.

00:51:49.285 --> 00:51:52.885
You see that everything is not ideal
like it was in Zrinjski.

00:51:53.047 --> 00:51:55.767
Or like it was in those
six months at Inter.

00:51:55.928 --> 00:52:00.008
You came into a situation where
you see... -That's not really the case.

00:52:00.257 --> 00:52:03.806
You practically don't know
who drinks and who pays.

00:52:04.010 --> 00:52:06.314
That was how it was
for six months.

00:52:06.495 --> 00:52:10.283
And when I came back after the injury,
it was already the end,

00:52:10.470 --> 00:52:13.501
everything had been in vain.

00:52:13.784 --> 00:52:18.298
Then I came back and played
two matches and the season ended.

00:52:19.920 --> 00:52:24.334
That was with Niko Kranjčar.
They actually...

00:52:27.974 --> 00:52:36.060
The journalists created this story about
the rivalry between Niko and you.

00:52:37.175 --> 00:52:42.969
As a coach, I noticed
that you two are artists,

00:52:43.406 --> 00:52:49.214
two creative people, geniuses,
who are best together on the field,

00:52:49.780 --> 00:52:52.211
when you are close to each other.

00:52:52.980 --> 00:52:56.620
And that's how we are
in the national team.

00:52:56.860 --> 00:53:02.420
Niko plays on the left, and you
keep it on the left side...

00:53:02.620 --> 00:53:08.059
And on the right side, Srna
and Ćorluka go on the attack.

00:53:08.460 --> 00:53:12.180
Later, you played together
in Tottenham.

00:53:13.020 --> 00:53:19.100
Two talented artists, two friends
who respect each other

00:53:20.551 --> 00:53:24.591
and work best together on the field,
because they understand each other.

00:53:24.800 --> 00:53:28.994
Yes, definitely. This was shown through
our matches in the national team,

00:53:29.172 --> 00:53:30.970
and later through Tottenham,

00:53:33.260 --> 00:53:37.380
that we worked phenomenally
together on the field.

00:53:38.540 --> 00:53:43.300
Off the field we had great
respect for each other.

00:53:44.260 --> 00:53:48.297
It was a pleasure to play with Niko,
because he is a great player.

00:53:48.458 --> 00:53:51.710
It is a pleasure to play with players
who see football in a similar way. -Yes.

00:53:51.884 --> 00:53:56.844
So that was the period until we played
together in the national team

00:53:57.373 --> 00:54:04.124
and at Tottenham, especially in the
national team, where a phenomenal

00:54:04.331 --> 00:54:09.691
climate and generation created itself,
and you contributed a lot to it.

00:54:11.580 --> 00:54:18.620
Maybe we lacked a bit of sporting luck
to make a big result with you,

00:54:18.860 --> 00:54:22.820
but later everything
came to be repaid.

00:54:22.961 --> 00:54:29.521
With Niko, creating a rivalry is normal,
especially when he was in Hajduk,

00:54:29.740 --> 00:54:35.100
and I was in Dinamo, but I never felt
that rivalry in that way.

00:54:35.721 --> 00:54:41.881
I respected him as a player
and as a person.

00:54:42.740 --> 00:54:46.460
And it was a pleasure
to compete against him.

00:54:47.380 --> 00:54:51.860
That was the way I looked
at our relationship.

00:54:52.620 --> 00:54:56.460
During that period
when you grow up,

00:54:56.980 --> 00:55:02.832
in Zagreb, you meet your wife Vanja,
the woman of your life.

00:55:04.460 --> 00:55:13.500
I am lucky to know your family.
It is a unique family.

00:55:13.793 --> 00:55:16.739
They are your Pentagon.

00:55:18.980 --> 00:55:22.060
Whenever someone asks me
about Luka Modrić,

00:55:22.340 --> 00:55:26.140
how normal he is,
my answer is the same.

00:55:26.420 --> 00:55:31.420
"Go and spend 5 minutes with
his family, with his mom and dad,

00:55:31.660 --> 00:55:34.540
and everything will be clear.
I don't have to explain anything."

00:55:34.820 --> 00:55:39.740
Parents often go crazy. Stipe
remained Stipe, he hasn't changed.

00:55:39.980 --> 00:55:42.620
Your mom was still
your mom, of course,

00:55:42.860 --> 00:55:49.260
and your sisters and your uncle.
They are your Pentagon, your pick,

00:55:49.540 --> 00:55:57.220
your base where you keep balance
in this crazy world, to stay normal

00:55:57.420 --> 00:56:00.580
and phenomenal.
Those are the foundations,

00:56:00.820 --> 00:56:06.740
there are no flaws at all. -That's
definitely the case, in every way.

00:56:06.980 --> 00:56:14.954
There are dad, mom, sisters and
an uncle who is like a father to me.

00:56:16.821 --> 00:56:20.798
They raised me to be like this.
When you see them,

00:56:20.977 --> 00:56:25.071
I can't be any different.
And I haven't changed at all.

00:56:25.321 --> 00:56:31.300
I don't think I'm anything special
because of what I've achieved.

00:56:31.518 --> 00:56:38.478
I'll continue to be a normal boy
who has his good and bad days.

00:56:39.460 --> 00:56:48.879
As a person, I progressed,
changed, but I didn't change the original

00:56:49.036 --> 00:56:53.596
that makes me who I am.
-You mature. -Yes, I mature.

00:56:54.460 --> 00:56:59.340
But sometimes people
don't like something

00:56:59.620 --> 00:57:02.340
that I do and say
that I've changed.

00:57:02.620 --> 00:57:07.660
But that's not the case.
They gave me peace and stability.

00:57:07.940 --> 00:57:14.860
I met Vanja while playing at Inter
and she gave me great stability.

00:57:15.100 --> 00:57:21.916
While she's at home, I can focus
on the field, on what's primary.

00:57:22.309 --> 00:57:29.462
That's not the case in today's world,
to have someone like that by your side.

00:57:29.603 --> 00:57:34.020
For someone to subordinate themselves
to you and your career as she did.

00:57:34.160 --> 00:57:40.360
As you said, she's my jackpot.
-Yes, jackpot.

00:57:40.692 --> 00:57:45.281
During that period,
you are doing really well.

00:57:45.515 --> 00:57:48.430
After Dinamo Zagreb fights
for the "league for fools",

00:57:48.700 --> 00:57:52.540
Josip Kuže returns to Dinamo Zagreb.
Then you become champions

00:57:52.900 --> 00:57:57.020
and it begins dominance
and lasts all that time.

00:57:57.420 --> 00:58:03.191
Unfortunately, it still is.
In principle, it was like that.

00:58:03.449 --> 00:58:06.158
At that time, you also played
for the youth national team,

00:58:06.285 --> 00:58:08.459
which achieved good results.

00:58:09.054 --> 00:58:11.605
Then you earned a call up
for the senior national team

00:58:11.683 --> 00:58:14.933
for the match against Argentina.
In 2006 you also went to the World Cup.

00:58:15.027 --> 00:58:17.996
You haven't played much,
but you still played.

00:58:18.131 --> 00:58:22.105
As I came to the national team,
you start playing for the senior team

00:58:22.377 --> 00:58:26.572
and immediately become
one of the main players.

00:58:26.682 --> 00:58:29.034
The national team played well,
your games were great.

00:58:29.183 --> 00:58:32.525
We qualified for Euro,
and that was your first competition

00:58:32.700 --> 00:58:36.100
where you played the main role.

00:58:40.180 --> 00:58:45.340
The beginning was triumphant, when you
score a penalty in the third minute.

00:58:45.580 --> 00:58:49.620
It's a big responsibility when you have
to take a penalty in the third minute.

00:58:49.860 --> 00:58:55.580
And the night before that match,
you and I had a conversation at Prater.

00:58:55.900 --> 00:58:59.140
Then we experienced that
disappointment against the Turkey.

00:58:59.380 --> 00:59:03.980
Even now, when we talk sometimes,
you still think about that match.

00:59:04.260 --> 00:59:09.060
I will never... Regardless of all
the other results that we later achieved

00:59:09.300 --> 00:59:13.580
and played in the League of Nations final.
That match can't be easily forgotten.

00:59:14.380 --> 00:59:17.700
It is one of the toughest...

00:59:20.780 --> 00:59:27.180
Not one for me, but it was the toughest
moment of my football career.

00:59:27.420 --> 00:59:31.540
You were still young at the time.
-I was young, but regardless...

00:59:31.820 --> 00:59:35.900
I wasn't ready, but the
game was really tough.

00:59:36.140 --> 00:59:41.020
It was hard to accept why it all
ended the way it did. How?

00:59:41.260 --> 00:59:44.867
What could we have done better?
Later, we thought a lot about

00:59:45.027 --> 00:59:47.733
whether everything could
have happened differently.

00:59:47.898 --> 00:59:50.278
If I did this, or if he did that.

00:59:51.432 --> 00:59:57.844
For the next few months
I was unable to function normally.

00:59:58.374 --> 01:00:05.374
Even when I moved to England
I was still thinkinh about that.

01:00:06.025 --> 01:00:08.781
It was not easy for us.

01:00:08.979 --> 01:00:14.898
You too can recall the situation
in the locker room after the match

01:00:15.093 --> 01:00:18.289
against the Turkish national team.
-Yes. -What was happening there.

01:00:19.975 --> 01:00:21.972
Such an atmosphere isn't usual
even at a funeral,

01:00:22.097 --> 01:00:23.697
like the one in our locker room.

01:00:23.835 --> 01:00:27.871
We probably had to lose in order
to win later. -Yes, I agree.

01:00:28.007 --> 01:00:30.127
At that moment,
we couldn't understand it.

01:00:30.266 --> 01:00:32.226
At that moment, we didn't
think about it, and even some

01:00:32.340 --> 01:00:34.761
people came into the locker room
to tell us that everything would be fine.

01:00:34.868 --> 01:00:38.410
We just looked at him and wondered,
what do you mean. Leave me alone.

01:00:38.707 --> 01:00:44.832
Everyone leave because I want to disappear.
However, that made us stronger.

01:00:45.007 --> 01:00:48.127
Without those failures,
I might not know

01:00:48.315 --> 01:00:53.707
how to appreciate the successes
we achieved later.

01:00:53.800 --> 01:00:58.324
It's something that's necessary,
no matter how much you don't want it.

01:00:58.653 --> 01:01:01.573
But you need it in order
to learn something from it.

01:01:01.780 --> 01:01:06.332
To come out stronger and be able
to rejoice more later. -Capitalize it.

01:01:06.418 --> 01:01:08.138
Yes and capitalize.

01:01:08.308 --> 01:01:12.433
In those qualifications you played
for a year and a half, and of course

01:01:12.559 --> 01:01:17.719
for Dinamo Zagreb when you played
the qualifiers for the Champions League.

01:01:17.881 --> 01:01:22.121
There you have experienced
some disappointments,

01:01:22.235 --> 01:01:26.020
I mean the game against Werder Bremen.
But you also had great victories.

01:01:26.229 --> 01:01:32.129
However, in these qualifiers against
England, against Russia,

01:01:32.332 --> 01:01:36.633
Israel and other national teams,
you simply came...

01:01:37.308 --> 01:01:40.071
I know this because
I follow that every day.

01:01:40.774 --> 01:01:50.607
You played well before too, but then you
became mature and aware of your quality.

01:01:51.814 --> 01:01:58.316
Yes, that was all... what I always
thought about myself.

01:01:58.830 --> 01:02:05.683
I proved myself by playing in the most
difficult matches with Dinamo

01:02:05.995 --> 01:02:09.620
in the Champions League,
and also in the domestic league

01:02:09.860 --> 01:02:14.980
matches against Hajduk.
Against England, against Russia.

01:02:16.380 --> 01:02:20.580
In such matches,
you can see who is who.

01:02:20.820 --> 01:02:25.060
Then the quality of the player is confirmed
and whether he can play at that level.

01:02:25.900 --> 01:02:30.435
There was also that match against
Germany. One of the better matches.

01:02:30.780 --> 01:02:33.940
I remember, and you probably
remember too,

01:02:34.069 --> 01:02:36.700
when we went to play at Wembley
after the match against Macedonia.

01:02:36.892 --> 01:02:40.572
Then I told you that we would crush them.
-No, that was in Čatež.

01:02:40.701 --> 01:02:44.013
At that time the Croatina national
team was preparing in Čatež.

01:02:44.154 --> 01:02:48.677
Yes, we were in Čatež. -After
we qualified following Macedonia,

01:02:48.776 --> 01:02:51.736
we arrived in Čatež. On Wednesday,
there was a match at Wembley,

01:02:51.865 --> 01:02:54.545
which technically didn't mean much to
us, but it does because it's Wembley.

01:02:54.667 --> 01:02:56.987
To them, it meant everything
because they're English.

01:02:57.116 --> 01:02:59.476
We were training on Monday,
it was muddy in Čatež

01:02:59.552 --> 01:03:01.512
because we had been
training there for eight days...

01:03:01.656 --> 01:03:05.096
We had already been playing in the mud.
-It was November...

01:03:05.225 --> 01:03:08.161
And you said to me,
all muddy from the pitch:

01:03:08.292 --> 01:03:11.812
"Can you imagine when we go out on
Wembley on Wednesday..."

01:03:11.950 --> 01:03:18.411
... how we'll destroy them...
And it really was like that. -Yes, yes.

01:03:19.900 --> 01:03:23.500
I'm not saying this now just
because I'm talking to you,

01:03:23.820 --> 01:03:27.580
but you, gave us,
younger players the confidence.

01:03:27.797 --> 01:03:31.839
We were so grateful to you,
and we wanted to return that.

01:03:32.972 --> 01:03:38.092
My feeling was that, when we played
poorly, we had let you down.

01:03:38.255 --> 01:03:45.050
We wanted to repay you for everything
you gave us, not just as a coach,

01:03:45.136 --> 01:03:49.011
but with your advice as well.
I still remember from the youth team,

01:03:49.136 --> 01:03:51.965
where you gave me
the captain's armband in Sweden,

01:03:52.121 --> 01:03:57.215
with players from the youngest age
groups, '83 and '84.

01:03:57.660 --> 01:04:05.410
Back then, Iniesta was just starting to
play for Barcelona,

01:04:05.634 --> 01:04:08.339
and on one of the first training
sessions, you said to me:

01:04:08.489 --> 01:04:12.332
"You're on the same level
as Iniesta, you're that level.

01:04:12.550 --> 01:04:16.910
He plays for Barcelona, but you can
get there." -He is a Spaniard.

01:04:17.137 --> 01:04:22.004
Imagine what was going through my mind
then, and how I felt toward you,

01:04:22.140 --> 01:04:26.300
and how much I would do
for you on the pitch.

01:04:26.580 --> 01:04:30.060
That's what carried us, especially the
younger ones, through those years,

01:04:30.260 --> 01:04:35.460
but also the older ones. We had a great
blend and balance with Robi, Kovač,

01:04:35.700 --> 01:04:41.500
Srna, who was already one of the older
players, Joe Šimunić, Dario Šimić,

01:04:41.916 --> 01:04:44.716
and others like Niko Kovač.

01:04:45.060 --> 01:04:49.220
We really had an incredible
atmosphere and balance.

01:04:49.721 --> 01:04:51.201
Yes, it was great.

01:04:51.700 --> 01:04:59.540
So, you signed for Tottenham before the
Euro, right? -Yes, before the Euro.

01:04:59.980 --> 01:05:05.060
But did it bother you?
Were you upset that you had to stay

01:05:05.300 --> 01:05:08.940
another year at Dinamo,
since out of the three of you,

01:05:09.220 --> 01:05:12.700
Čarli and Dudu had gone to
Arsenal and City a year earlier,

01:05:12.940 --> 01:05:15.780
and you had to stay?
-Yes, they left that season.

01:05:16.060 --> 01:05:18.940
It didn't bother me because
I wanted to stay at Dinamo,

01:05:19.117 --> 01:05:21.557
but I was disappointed...
-... because they left?

01:05:21.736 --> 01:05:24.736
I was disappointed,
but no matter that they left,

01:05:25.000 --> 01:05:28.240
I still wanted to stay
because I thought I could

01:05:28.409 --> 01:05:31.209
achieve something with Dinamo in Europe.

01:05:31.410 --> 01:05:35.483
Dinamo had that ambition, at least
that's how it was presented to us.

01:05:35.650 --> 01:05:41.450
But then, the first offer came,
Čarli went abroad, my best friend.

01:05:41.800 --> 01:05:47.720
So now I'm without one friend.
Dudu left too.

01:05:48.140 --> 01:05:51.500
And then you start thinking about why
when we're talking about

01:05:51.740 --> 01:05:55.660
wanting to do something big,
and now your key players are leaving.

01:05:55.900 --> 01:05:58.860
Despite that, I still wanted to stay

01:05:59.100 --> 01:06:04.140
because I was enjoying my time at
Dinamo. It was really nice there,

01:06:04.420 --> 01:06:10.700
but then came the halfway point,
Vukojević was sold, if I'm not mistaken,

01:06:10.854 --> 01:06:14.454
and then someone else was sold. And then
you think, 'What am I doing here?'

01:06:14.646 --> 01:06:21.182
and I wanted to leave. That's when I got
a little upset and had a small conflict,

01:06:21.348 --> 01:06:25.549
not a major one, but I was angry at
the club because I wanted to leave.

01:06:25.713 --> 01:06:31.416
Then Chelsea appeared, and when
the club didn't want to let me go,

01:06:31.685 --> 01:06:35.645
Tottenham came in June,
and I immediately knew,

01:06:35.980 --> 01:06:45.100
when that option appeared, knowing
the club well and said, 'I'm going.'

01:06:45.878 --> 01:06:47.638
That was it.

01:06:48.580 --> 01:06:53.900
And now, you and Vanja
go to London, a huge city.

01:06:54.500 --> 01:06:58.660
The club is part of the big five, right?

01:06:59.220 --> 01:07:05.660
The league is what it is.
It's a big transfer, right?

01:07:05.900 --> 01:07:10.060
You're already the guy for the job,

01:07:10.340 --> 01:07:13.420
and it helps with the English the most
when you've already beat them once.

01:07:13.660 --> 01:07:22.380
We were in the qualifiers, came through,
and the start was tricky.

01:07:22.660 --> 01:07:28.180
It doesn't help that we're in the group
with the English again, and we lost 4-1.

01:07:28.620 --> 01:07:35.340
The coach is Ramos, and some small
stories start about your fitness,

01:07:36.420 --> 01:07:39.780
justifying why you didn't go to
Newcastle, Manchester, and others,

01:07:40.060 --> 01:07:44.420
but rather to Tottenham. The issue
of physical fitness was created,

01:07:44.660 --> 01:07:49.740
that's the smaller struggle
that doesn’t last long.

01:07:50.020 --> 01:07:54.260
Then a good thing happens again,
Harry Redknapp comes as coach.

01:07:54.580 --> 01:08:03.220
Yes. At Tottenham it didn’t start well.
First of all, preseason ruined me.

01:08:03.420 --> 01:08:09.420
Why? -Because it was one of
the hardest preseasons of my life.

01:08:10.020 --> 01:08:18.220
Maybe the reason was that after
the Euro, after that trauma,

01:08:18.500 --> 01:08:22.820
I didn’t want to hear about football.
In that one free month,

01:08:23.060 --> 01:08:27.900
I did nothing. Normally I go crazy
when I’m not doing anything.

01:08:28.100 --> 01:08:31.180
I have to. Either I play basketball
or I play tennis. That month

01:08:31.380 --> 01:08:37.780
I did nothing. I’d had enough
of football after the loss to Turkey.

01:08:38.020 --> 01:08:41.860
That was a trauma. Then I came
there, preseason, running,

01:08:42.060 --> 01:08:46.660
three trainings a day. At 7:30
in the morning on golf fields

01:08:46.860 --> 01:08:52.620
in Valencia. We run, Zokora,
Gilberto, the Brazilian and me.

01:08:52.980 --> 01:08:57.483
Zokora a kilometre ahead of me.
He can run for three days.

01:08:59.180 --> 01:09:02.820
Then at 10:30 training on the beach,
and football in the evening.

01:09:03.060 --> 01:09:05.140
Legs like wood,
you can’t do anything.

01:09:05.580 --> 01:09:09.580
I had a small knee injury there
and the season didn’t start well.

01:09:09.820 --> 01:09:15.620
We lost the first few matches,
I think we had just one point.

01:09:17.300 --> 01:09:23.140
After, if I'm not mistaken,
a few rounds, Harry Redknapp

01:09:23.420 --> 01:09:28.100
comes as coach. We play at home
against Bolton, and since he

01:09:28.420 --> 01:09:32.220
arrived the night before,
he wasn’t supposed to be on the bench.

01:09:32.460 --> 01:09:35.980
But he, as an old fox, sits
on the bench… -Bolton? -Yes.

01:09:36.220 --> 01:09:43.940
He sets the team and we play great.
We win 2-0. That’s when it started.

01:09:45.100 --> 01:09:50.614
I think we played the most
beautiful football then.

01:09:51.140 --> 01:09:56.660
We beat Liverpool at home.
That famous 4-4 at Emirates,

01:09:56.900 --> 01:10:00.500
right after that. We really played
amazing football with Harry.

01:10:00.780 --> 01:10:11.380
He loved Croatians and he really
was perfect for the team we had.

01:10:12.333 --> 01:10:16.820
A real expert, a cool guy,
he understands football.

01:10:17.100 --> 01:10:22.340
The type of English coach who says
what needs to be said, watches training.

01:10:22.540 --> 01:10:26.180
He coached less, but
stepped in when necessary.

01:10:26.373 --> 01:10:30.653
He gives you exact instructions
on what to do on the pitch.

01:10:30.783 --> 01:10:35.783
He was ideal for us. -He loved
Croatians? -He did. He always

01:10:35.927 --> 01:10:40.653
spoke nicely about you,
about Štimac. -At one point

01:10:40.761 --> 01:10:43.684
there were four of you.
-They called us Cro Tottenham.

01:10:43.800 --> 01:10:51.060
Plete, Niko, Čarli and me. Four.
-He’s a coach people often underrate,

01:10:52.460 --> 01:10:59.700
and he coached me at West Ham.
He adopted that "biggest enemy" thing.

01:10:59.980 --> 01:11:04.980
It’s not that he brags about it,
but he’s a coach who likes to put

01:11:05.740 --> 01:11:11.660
as many good players as possible
on the pitch. -Yes. -He isn’t afraid

01:11:11.900 --> 01:11:16.660
to play you, Niko, this one,
that one. -He has no problem.

01:11:16.980 --> 01:11:21.780
He plays the ones who love to play.
-He really understands football.

01:11:21.980 --> 01:11:25.540
I think it’s unbelievable that
he never coached England.

01:11:25.780 --> 01:11:29.620
I think he would’ve been ideal
for that generation…

01:11:29.820 --> 01:11:33.060
The one they had back then.
-That would’ve been the ideal coach,

01:11:33.300 --> 01:11:38.916
but why it didn’t happen…
-Those are things outside football.

01:11:39.420 --> 01:11:45.860
Then Tottenham, always Tottenham,
right, goes to the Champions League.

01:11:46.100 --> 01:11:49.460
That match with City…
-After 60+ years.

01:11:49.700 --> 01:11:54.500
In the Champions League they play
great, all of it. Milan and Real, right?

01:11:54.637 --> 01:11:57.277
Yes. -We lost to Real
in the quarterfinals.

01:11:58.820 --> 01:12:05.300
And then you only grow and grow.
That stigma disappears, you get

01:12:05.580 --> 01:12:11.740
big praise from Alex Ferguson
and others… I forgot our talk,

01:12:14.820 --> 01:12:21.780
but I remembered it the other day.
Chelsea calls, and you’re close

01:12:22.700 --> 01:12:27.540
to leaving, 2011…
-2011. -To Chelsea.

01:12:27.780 --> 01:12:36.700
That says a lot about your
character. You forgot it,

01:12:36.980 --> 01:12:42.789
and so did I, and only later I remembered.
We played a match in Dublin.

01:12:42.960 --> 01:12:45.960
Friendly match.
-Against Ireland, yes.

01:12:46.083 --> 01:12:49.615
The one in August,
when the transfer window is open,

01:12:49.840 --> 01:12:54.138
and the league had already started.
You said you wanted to talk to me.

01:12:54.479 --> 01:12:59.107
What is it about? Chelsea.
You said you wanted to go to Chelsea.

01:12:59.253 --> 01:13:03.435
Said it publicly. -You saw it as your
big step forward. Is that right? -Yes.

01:13:03.716 --> 01:13:07.156
But you were a Tottenham player.
We know that Tottenham

01:13:07.404 --> 01:13:11.964
is very difficult to negotiate with,
especially with English clubs.

01:13:12.832 --> 01:13:19.352
You played some sort of warm-up match,
Tottenham against some team,

01:13:19.506 --> 01:13:23.786
and you played very well.
You even celebrated the goal you scored.

01:13:24.100 --> 01:13:27.540
Then you tell me: "Boss,
they called me from Chelsea...",

01:13:27.820 --> 01:13:32.380
I won’t say who, because it doesn’t matter,
"... and they said that a player who wants

01:13:32.660 --> 01:13:38.100
to leave the club doesn’t behave like that."
I said, "Alright Luka,

01:13:38.380 --> 01:13:44.100
but tell them that you are Luka Modrić,
and if they want to buy you,

01:13:44.182 --> 01:13:47.826
then they should buy you",
and not expect you to punch the coach

01:13:47.914 --> 01:13:49.874
in the head just because you want to go.

01:13:49.988 --> 01:13:56.510
Nowadays it’s considered normal
not to show up for pre-season, etc.,

01:13:56.780 --> 01:14:01.340
and you want to go to Chelsea,
because Chelsea was top at that time.

01:14:01.660 --> 01:14:08.260
But you won’t do things
that shouldn’t be done. -Yes.

01:14:09.610 --> 01:14:14.231
I said that publicly,
but maybe I shouldn’t have,

01:14:14.387 --> 01:14:22.060
because I was happy at Tottenham,
and my relationship with the club

01:14:22.420 --> 01:14:24.980
and the fans was phenomenal.

01:14:25.380 --> 01:14:31.180
But at one moment I felt
that I had reached a certain level

01:14:31.420 --> 01:14:36.900
and that I wanted to take a step forward
so I could progress further in my career.

01:14:37.140 --> 01:14:39.587
But simply, Tottenham was firm.

01:14:39.834 --> 01:14:45.056
The club president was very strict
already in the first meeting.

01:14:47.853 --> 01:14:51.179
During the conversation
he made it clear

01:14:51.301 --> 01:14:54.392
that there was no chance
he would let me go.

01:14:56.870 --> 01:15:00.016
After that, I continued to behave normally,
as if nothing was happening,

01:15:00.105 --> 01:15:02.124
because I knew it would be difficult.

01:15:02.231 --> 01:15:05.111
Both clubs are from London,
there’s also the rivalry...

01:15:05.366 --> 01:15:09.046
I wanted it, even though I knew
it would be very difficult.

01:15:09.207 --> 01:15:11.727
In the end it didn’t happen,
and I continued to play

01:15:11.914 --> 01:15:16.941
as if nothing had happened. I played
maybe one of my best seasons that year.

01:15:17.143 --> 01:15:19.891
We finished in fourth place,
but Chelsea won

01:15:20.028 --> 01:15:23.251
the Champions League that year.
Because it wasn’t like today,

01:15:23.360 --> 01:15:26.024
where if you finish fourth
you go through no matter what.

01:15:26.136 --> 01:15:28.971
You go to the Champions League, yes.
-Chelsea was in fifth place,

01:15:29.073 --> 01:15:32.019
but since they won, they qualified
for the Champions League,

01:15:32.153 --> 01:15:36.425
and Tottenham didn’t. So the season
was phenomenal, and then a year later...

01:15:36.552 --> 01:15:39.362
In the end it turned out
that it was better that way.

01:15:39.512 --> 01:15:43.191
Probably, if you had gone to Chelsea...
There would be no Real Madrid move.

01:15:43.348 --> 01:15:46.863
At least not for another year.
-Certainly not. So it turned out perfectly.

01:15:47.015 --> 01:15:50.113
Chelsea doesn’t sell players that easily.
-That’s something I always keep in mind.

01:15:50.210 --> 01:15:52.410
Who knows why something
is good when it doesn’t happen.

01:15:52.570 --> 01:15:55.714
And in the end it turned out
why it was good. -Yes.

01:15:55.896 --> 01:16:02.656
Before that we had another
competition with the national team,

01:16:02.848 --> 01:16:06.980
in which we didn’t qualify.
That was in 2010, right?

01:16:07.520 --> 01:16:12.620
And then in 2012 we went to the EURO.
It was the same situation as in 2008.

01:16:12.911 --> 01:16:20.015
Only now in the same group were
the Italians, the Irish, and the Spanish,

01:16:20.191 --> 01:16:27.286
with Iniesta, Xavi, and Pirlo there as well,
but by then you already knew in your mind

01:16:27.438 --> 01:16:33.059
that you were of that level, only you
were Croatian, and they were Spanish.

01:16:33.309 --> 01:16:40.509
You know that I have great confidence
in myself, my qualities, abilities, etc.,

01:16:40.649 --> 01:16:44.543
but when you play against such teams
you have to know everything about yourself,

01:16:44.689 --> 01:16:48.009
and you have to play
against such players and show

01:16:48.118 --> 01:16:52.468
whether you are actually at that
level or not. And we played excellent,

01:16:52.593 --> 01:16:56.233
but we were in a group
that ended being finals.

01:16:56.386 --> 01:16:59.663
And we could have beaten
either of them, for example.

01:16:59.796 --> 01:17:03.054
We have we played excellent against them.
Unfortunately, it didn’t go our way

01:17:03.199 --> 01:17:05.959
and we were eliminated
in the group stage.

01:17:06.965 --> 01:17:10.710
But we played good football,
very good.

01:17:13.740 --> 01:17:18.380
That was the match against Spain
where, as we later found out,

01:17:18.620 --> 01:17:26.625
Mourinho finally came to watch you.
And you played brilliantly.

01:17:26.773 --> 01:17:29.914
It was a phenomenal match.
That one and the one against Turkey,

01:17:30.053 --> 01:17:36.820
those are two matches we lost, so they’re
not talked about as top performances.

01:17:37.053 --> 01:17:42.293
But we talked about it you played
excellently in both matches.

01:17:42.494 --> 01:17:46.414
Against Turkey you set up Oli
for that chance over the crossbar

01:17:46.481 --> 01:17:48.601
and then you score. -Krasnić, yes.

01:17:48.708 --> 01:17:58.161
And the one against Spain was great.
And then you go to Real? -Yes.

01:17:58.309 --> 01:18:04.989
Is it true that president Levy
promised you, a year ago,

01:18:05.173 --> 01:18:09.708
that if Real called you,
you would go, or isn't that so?

01:18:10.310 --> 01:18:12.254
It's true that he promised me.

01:18:12.403 --> 01:18:16.997
When Chelsea didn't happen,
he promised me half the season.

01:18:17.194 --> 01:18:23.029
I insisted on moving on, because
Chelsea wanted me for next year,

01:18:23.111 --> 01:18:25.151
and I said I wanted to go.

01:18:25.266 --> 01:18:30.599
We had negotiations to extend
and sign a new contract.

01:18:31.220 --> 01:18:36.200
However, at one point,
I don't know why,

01:18:36.518 --> 01:18:42.154
he told me that the only club he
would let me go to was Real Madrid.

01:18:44.060 --> 01:18:47.940
No matter how much you
believe in yourself,

01:18:48.074 --> 01:18:51.274
Real Madrid sounds unattainable.
You think it's too far for you.

01:18:51.413 --> 01:18:57.828
Real is special. I spent 13 years there
and I know what I'm talking about.

01:19:00.500 --> 01:19:04.620
I tell him that I want it too,
but I might not be able to go to Real.

01:19:04.919 --> 01:19:08.159
He kept repeating that it was
the only club he'd let me go to.

01:19:08.306 --> 01:19:10.146
I tell him: "Okay, fine".

01:19:10.324 --> 01:19:15.214
We had a conversation after that,
and Vanja was there.

01:19:15.317 --> 01:19:19.757
He repeated it again,
and I say: "OK!"

01:19:20.060 --> 01:19:24.380
Then came the Euro and
the preparations. We were in Rovinj.

01:19:24.700 --> 01:19:31.070
But even before going to Rovinj,
they called me to tell me

01:19:31.408 --> 01:19:36.688
that Real wanted me.
I was delighted!

01:19:39.580 --> 01:19:45.580
The contact started in May,
towards the end of the season.

01:19:45.983 --> 01:19:52.303
Or we were on vacation, preparing.
I knew Real was interested.

01:19:52.417 --> 01:19:54.537
I also talked to the coach.

01:19:55.625 --> 01:20:00.545
However, going there was not easy.

01:20:01.060 --> 01:20:07.660
Regardless of what he allowed me,
the negotiations were difficult and long.

01:20:08.780 --> 01:20:16.460
You probably know how I
behaved at that moment.

01:20:18.926 --> 01:20:24.566
It wasn't difficult to take that step.
But it was difficult for me.

01:20:24.878 --> 01:20:33.568
However, I had a promise,
that was in my head.

01:20:33.763 --> 01:20:40.070
If someone gives me a promise,
a hand shake, I expect them to keep it.

01:20:40.232 --> 01:20:48.512
I understand negotiations and agreements,
but, really, it was difficult and long.

01:20:48.980 --> 01:20:52.300
And then I decided to take that step.

01:20:52.620 --> 01:20:56.940
I was ready at that moment
not to play anymore.

01:20:57.180 --> 01:21:04.050
What you didn't want to do a year ago,
because you felt it would be too much,

01:21:04.159 --> 01:21:09.901
then you felt betrayed, because, after all,
that's what you were promised.

01:21:10.088 --> 01:21:14.808
That's right. -The club chairman
promised you that.

01:21:14.976 --> 01:21:18.103
It was difficult for me
because of my relationship

01:21:18.266 --> 01:21:20.731
and history with Tottenham
and the fans.

01:21:20.920 --> 01:21:27.555
It's not me, it's not my character,
but I didn't see any other solution.

01:21:28.685 --> 01:21:32.525
And that's it. -It's your character.
You did the same thing twice.

01:21:32.671 --> 01:21:37.024
Leaving Dinamo, you're going last?
-Yes. -Instead of first.

01:21:38.740 --> 01:21:43.780
It's the same here. I gave you everything,
but don't tease me anymore.

01:21:43.980 --> 01:21:47.303
That's true. -You gave everything,
and too much.

01:21:47.425 --> 01:21:50.547
Everything has its limits.
-And now it's enough! -That's right.

01:21:50.764 --> 01:21:54.281
And you're coming to Real.

01:21:56.293 --> 01:21:58.773
Where do you see your advantage?

01:21:58.926 --> 01:22:02.852
Where do you see that you have what
this other opponent doesn't have?

01:22:02.983 --> 01:22:08.180
The ones who put me as the last
midfielder were you and Harry Redknapp.

01:22:08.319 --> 01:22:16.249
We didn't talk to Mandža in those
years the way we used to.

01:22:16.506 --> 01:22:21.107
I told her that we would play
a phenomenal World Cup.

01:22:21.284 --> 01:22:24.364
We'll do the best,
and I'll be the best. -No!

01:22:24.611 --> 01:22:29.291
Huge moment of your national team
career was the match against Denmark.

01:22:31.760 --> 01:22:36.244
Just like that... Blow, blow.
That is impossible.

